41:05.920 --> 41:06.739
Hi.

41:08.540 --> 41:09.586
My dad said you called.

41:09.960 --> 41:12.417
And I heard what happened
in court today and...

41:13.050 --> 41:15.041
I don't know, I just wanted
to reach out, you know,

41:15.130 --> 41:16.631
to see if there's anything I could do.

41:19.100 --> 41:19.919
Come in.

41:22.100 --> 41:25.228
I think it's a tolerance thing.
I don't know.

41:26.520 --> 41:30.012
-I've only ever shot up a couple times.
-You could've fucking died.

41:30.110 --> 41:31.099
[scoffs]

41:31.530 --> 41:33.600
Like anyone would even care
at this point.

41:33.860 --> 41:35.441
Dude, don't joke about that.

41:37.660 --> 41:38.558
Shit.

41:40.620 --> 41:41.530
Sorry.

41:44.080 --> 41:45.570
Hey, hey.

41:46.540 --> 41:47.359
Drink this.

42:04.480 --> 42:05.595
Where's the scar?

42:06.440 --> 42:07.304
Oh, it's...

42:08.810 --> 42:09.890
There's scars.

42:10.900 --> 42:13.892
But they're under my hair.
That's why I grew it out.

42:16.610 --> 42:18.316
Yeah, I remember how it used to be.

42:19.820 --> 42:21.868
When you first started at Liberty,

42:22.620 --> 42:26.408
some of the guys were like,
"That hair makes him a fag."

42:26.830 --> 42:31.415
But I was like, "That's fucking stupid."

42:33.630 --> 42:35.416
Well, that's super kind of you.

42:36.760 --> 42:37.670
Yeah, well...

42:40.640 --> 42:41.504
Whatever.

42:47.180 --> 42:49.398
You're still in love with Jessica,
aren't you?

42:51.940 --> 42:53.066
It doesn't matter.

42:54.020 --> 42:56.272
Look at you. It clearly does.

42:58.030 --> 42:59.019
[door opens]

43:01.950 --> 43:03.156
What the hell happened?

43:04.080 --> 43:07.072
He shot up and then he almost choked
on his own puke.

43:07.660 --> 43:10.322
What the fuck is wrong with you, Justin?
You were just clean--

43:10.420 --> 43:11.910
Leave him alone, okay?

43:12.630 --> 43:14.120
What? Now you're defending him?

43:14.210 --> 43:16.917
Yeah, what the hell were you thinking
with the tapes, Clay?

43:17.010 --> 43:18.875
You have any idea
what you did to Jessica?

43:18.970 --> 43:21.131
Yeah, I was trying to get justice
for Hannah.

43:21.470 --> 43:23.426
And I'm sorry if it hurt Jessica,

43:23.510 --> 43:25.671
but maybe it's time for her truth
to come out, too.

43:25.760 --> 43:29.139
What the fuck gives you the right
to decide what needs to come out?

43:31.650 --> 43:35.063
Look, I've done everything I can,

43:36.820 --> 43:39.027
everything I can think of
to make things right.

43:40.610 --> 43:42.237
But I can't do it alone.

43:45.160 --> 43:45.979
Okay?

43:46.660 --> 43:48.196
Look, I'm sorry about the tapes.

43:48.700 --> 43:50.656
But it's gonna get worse
before it gets better.

43:52.330 --> 43:53.410
And I need you guys.

43:55.340 --> 43:57.376
[Caleb] Turn your hands.
There you go, good hit.

43:58.590 --> 43:59.409
Yeah.

44:01.180 --> 44:02.078
Wow!

44:02.470 --> 44:05.291
-You did need to come in.
-Yeah. I feel better already.

44:05.600 --> 44:08.512
Ah. Well, the night is young.
It could get even better.

44:08.600 --> 44:09.476
-Oh, yeah?
-Yeah.

44:09.560 --> 44:10.595
What you got in mind?

44:11.100 --> 44:11.930
Oh!

44:12.600 --> 44:15.307
Hey! Hey, I didn't know
you were coming in today.

44:16.070 --> 44:18.220
Lucas, this is Tony. Tony, this is Lucas.

44:18.530 --> 44:20.566
Oh, hey, man. Good to meet you.

44:23.360 --> 44:26.272
Yeah, man. It's good to meet you, too.

44:28.080 --> 44:29.115
I'll talk to you later.

44:29.200 --> 44:31.498
I should get out of here anyway.
I'm pretty tired.

44:32.120 --> 44:32.950
Hey.

44:33.710 --> 44:35.371
Have we trained together before?

44:36.170 --> 44:38.707
No, I don't, uh, I don't think so.

44:40.590 --> 44:41.579
Have a good night.

44:44.890 --> 44:46.209
[Olivia] We don't always know

44:47.470 --> 44:49.210
everything a kid is going through.

44:49.520 --> 44:50.339
[knock at door]

44:51.230 --> 44:53.596
Hey, buddy. We agreed. Door open, yeah?

44:53.980 --> 44:56.141
-It was open.
-No, it was almost closed.

44:56.230 --> 44:59.108
We agreed 45 degrees open
all the time, all right?

44:59.480 --> 45:01.937
Then last month,
we negotiated down to 30.

45:02.030 --> 45:05.602
It was at three just now,
so keep it open, all right?

45:06.280 --> 45:07.190
Wait, Dad?

45:07.700 --> 45:11.613
I'm really sorry about last night.
I didn't mean to ruin the party.

45:13.080 --> 45:14.069
Oh, buddy.

45:18.460 --> 45:21.873
You didn't.
And I feel like I owe you an apology.

45:22.630 --> 45:25.793
Because I think
I've been pushing you too hard.

45:26.510 --> 45:29.297
No, I think maybe it's a good thing.

45:30.350 --> 45:33.672
Because today I, like,
I really pushed myself

45:33.770 --> 45:35.180
and it kind of turned out okay.

45:35.600 --> 45:38.262
-That's great.
-Yeah, and my memory's getting better.

45:39.900 --> 45:42.642
Good, well, the doctor didn't say
you were stuck, right?

45:42.730 --> 45:46.689
He said that your recovery
would be unpredictable,

45:46.780 --> 45:48.566
but there's always hope.

45:48.660 --> 45:49.866
-Yeah, I know.
-Yeah.

45:50.080 --> 45:53.652
Um, so, last night, with that video game,

45:53.750 --> 45:57.208
it actually started making me remember
this other one, Desert Duty.

45:57.880 --> 46:02.374
So, I was thinking, um,
just maybe if I play that one again,

46:02.460 --> 46:04.291
it would actually help me remember more.

46:05.170 --> 46:08.333
-That's a shooter game, Desert Duty ?
-Yeah, I know, Dad.

46:08.430 --> 46:10.341
But it's not like that. I just...

46:11.930 --> 46:13.966
There's something that I gotta remember.

46:17.190 --> 46:20.148
Yeah, buddy, I don't know.

46:22.570 --> 46:23.605
Yeah, no, I know.

46:25.190 --> 46:29.103
I get it. It was probably stupid anyway.

46:31.910 --> 46:34.231
-I should probably get some sleep.
-All right.

46:35.160 --> 46:36.821
-Night.
-Night.

46:41.380 --> 46:46.158
[Olivia] But, kids, they don't always
tell you everything they're feeling.

46:56.770 --> 47:01.184
"I'm saying that the house is on fire,
and all I know how to do is write poems.

47:01.270 --> 47:05.525
All I know how to do is arrange flowers
on the table of a burning home.

47:05.730 --> 47:09.143
I am pressing against the frame.
I am chanting the right words.

47:10.570 --> 47:12.947
I am gripping my fists
and letting them go."

47:14.080 --> 47:15.069
Wow.

47:16.750 --> 47:17.865
Hannah wrote that?

47:18.250 --> 47:19.706
I must have read it a million times.

47:19.790 --> 47:22.247
The whole time,
I thought it was about that school.

47:22.750 --> 47:25.799
The suffocating, oh, my God,
it's right there in front of me.

47:26.300 --> 47:29.212
The burning home, the flowers...

47:31.260 --> 47:32.830
It was about her dad's affair.

47:34.350 --> 47:35.669
There she was, trying to comfort me,

47:35.760 --> 47:37.307
when I should've been
trying to comfort her.

47:37.390 --> 47:38.880
I mean, why didn't I see it?

47:38.980 --> 47:41.551
Olivia, you can't blame yourself.
This is Andy's fault.

47:41.650 --> 47:44.266
Jackie, please don't tell me
how to feel right now.

47:49.360 --> 47:51.021
-I'm sorry.
-You're right.

47:51.280 --> 47:55.159
No, I'm sorry. It just--
It's more complicated than that.

47:55.240 --> 47:56.616
I didn't mean to overstep.

47:59.160 --> 48:01.708
You know,
I think maybe I should head to bed.

48:02.040 --> 48:04.201
-No, no, no.
-No, it's been a long day.

48:04.460 --> 48:06.496
Really, I need to get some rest.

48:07.630 --> 48:09.200
It was nice meeting you, Jessica.

48:22.480 --> 48:23.299
Well...

48:26.770 --> 48:27.680
[sighs deeply]

48:29.690 --> 48:31.271
You must think I'm an idiot,

48:31.360 --> 48:33.658
wanting to protect a man
who doesn't deserve it.

48:35.370 --> 48:36.234
I get it.

48:37.740 --> 48:40.368
I mean, I really get it.

48:41.910 --> 48:42.956
You love him, right?

48:43.290 --> 48:47.579
Despite everything, and it's crazy,
but you love him.

48:50.050 --> 48:50.869
I do.

48:53.680 --> 48:55.671
Even though he hurt you so bad.

49:05.940 --> 49:07.476
You know, Jessica, if there's...

49:09.400 --> 49:11.777
If there's anything
you ever wanna talk about...

49:14.700 --> 49:17.237
Sometimes I think
if Hannah would have come to me,

49:20.080 --> 49:21.991
maybe things would have been different.

49:24.960 --> 49:27.702
Maybe it was too painful for her
to talk about it.

49:31.550 --> 49:34.087
Maybe she kept it all in
to protect herself.

49:37.550 --> 49:39.177
I'm not good at that.

49:40.470 --> 49:44.634
The more I think about it,
she was really brave.

49:45.060 --> 49:48.689
Oh, but, honey,
we both know that didn't work.

49:49.520 --> 49:50.646
Keeping it in,

49:52.110 --> 49:53.179
that's not brave.

49:53.780 --> 49:56.408
Feeling the pain, facing it...

49:57.910 --> 49:59.366
that takes courage.

49:59.700 --> 50:01.361
It's okay to let it out.

50:05.960 --> 50:06.995
It's okay.

50:11.420 --> 50:12.296
[sobs]

50:20.430 --> 50:22.716
[Olivia] Not a day passes
during this trial...

50:23.140 --> 50:24.050
It's okay.

50:24.140 --> 50:26.096
...in the months it took to get here

50:26.180 --> 50:29.559
that I don't wish I could have wrapped
my arms around her

50:29.650 --> 50:31.561
and told her it would be okay.

50:32.770 --> 50:34.351
But I never had that chance.

50:35.320 --> 50:37.390
Why didn't you tell us he was on drugs?

50:38.240 --> 50:39.901
He was getting better, okay?

50:40.530 --> 50:43.158
Anyway, I didn't even know about the drugs
when I first brought him here.

50:43.240 --> 50:45.242
-Should we call social services?
-No. Dad!

50:45.330 --> 50:48.538
Call social services, he disappears
into the system, he doesn't testify.

50:48.620 --> 50:50.030
Jesus, is that what we care about?

50:50.130 --> 50:52.030
No, I care about keeping the kids safe,

50:52.130 --> 50:54.246
which is hard to do
when they're both fighting us.

50:54.340 --> 50:56.968
-How am I fighting you?
-The Register called me today, Clay.

50:57.050 --> 50:58.870
Those audio files were watermarked.

50:59.090 --> 51:00.717
You stole them from my computer.

51:00.800 --> 51:02.631
You told me you weren't working
on the case.

51:02.850 --> 51:04.841
-That's no excuse.
-You told Sonya.

51:05.180 --> 51:07.592
About Zach texting Hannah.
That's how they knew everything.

51:07.850 --> 51:08.726
Is that true?

51:08.810 --> 51:11.517
She's a colleague.
I pointed her in a direction.

51:11.610 --> 51:13.726
-It's hardly the same thing.
-It's worse.

51:13.820 --> 51:17.028
You endangered my job,
my license, our livelihood.

51:17.110 --> 51:18.236
You ruined my fucking life!

51:18.320 --> 51:21.483
Jesus, you sound like children.
And there's just one child here.

51:21.570 --> 51:24.983
-What is that supposed to mean?
-Clay needs us to be his parents now.

51:25.080 --> 51:27.537
-I don't need anything from you guys.
-Clay, go to your room.

51:27.620 --> 51:28.450
What?

51:29.160 --> 51:31.537
-How is that fair?
-Go to your goddamn room!

51:32.040 --> 51:32.995
Now!

51:38.420 --> 51:40.752
[Matt] Enough is enough.
This family will not be destroyed.

51:40.840 --> 51:44.003
Not for any case, not for any other
parents' kid, not by drugs.

51:44.100 --> 51:46.842
We will not let this happen.
I get it, you're mad.

51:46.930 --> 51:49.012
I'm mad at him, too, but he is a child!

51:55.520 --> 51:58.489
[Olivia] How can you fix something
if you don't know what's broken?

52:00.860 --> 52:02.157
Hannah didn't tell us.

52:05.950 --> 52:06.780
[Hannah] Clay.

52:10.750 --> 52:11.569
No.

52:13.290 --> 52:16.168
You don't talk.
You don't get to say anything.

52:16.500 --> 52:20.163
This is your fucking fault, Hannah.
This mess started with you.

52:20.260 --> 52:23.923
I put out the tapes, and that was stupid,
but you made them.

52:24.640 --> 52:26.676
-You fucked up people's lives!
-I know.

52:27.060 --> 52:29.096
-I'm sorry.
-Are you?

52:30.060 --> 52:31.129
Are you sorry?

52:31.230 --> 52:34.188
That doesn't do a fucking bit of good
because you are gone!

52:34.730 --> 52:38.439
You killed yourself
and you didn't fucking care.

52:38.530 --> 52:41.101
-I did!
-No, or you never would've done it.

52:41.360 --> 52:45.273
I was hurting,
and I didn't think about who I might hurt.

52:45.370 --> 52:47.656
You did an evil thing.

52:52.870 --> 52:53.916
Get the fuck out.

52:59.800 --> 53:01.506
